==============================================================================

==============================================================================
🧠 PURPOSE
==============================================================================
This closing workflow locks chat, classifies attendance, gathers the stream’s
analytics, calculates duration and retention, builds a formatted report, saves it
to Documents, optionally sends it through SMTP, and clears SeenUsers.

Long-term AttendanceHistory is preserved for future returning-viewer calculations.

==============================================================================
🔄 SYSTEM FLOW
==============================================================================
STEP 1: CHAT SHUTDOWN
--------------------------------
- Posts a closing message, waits five seconds, clears chat, and enables emote-only, subscriber-only, and slow mode.

STEP 2: ATTENDANCE SUMMARY
--------------------------------
- Reads SeenUsers and AttendanceHistory.
- Classifies attendees as returning or newly recorded and stores analytics.attendanceSummaryJson.

STEP 3: ANALYTICS COLLECTION
--------------------------------
- Loads chat, subscription details, follows, raids, bits, and the session start time.
- Removes excluded accounts from report collections.

STEP 4: METRIC CALCULATION
--------------------------------
- Calculates duration, messages per minute, top chatter, retention, and category totals.

STEP 5: REPORT OUTPUT
--------------------------------
- Creates analytics.finalSummaryJson and a formatted text report.
- Saves the report in Documents\StreamSummaries and optionally sends it through SMTP.

STEP 6: SESSION CLEANUP
--------------------------------
- Clears SeenUsers and posts the final locked-chat message.

